The article is a statement by the U.S. Treasury Department regarding General Motors' dealer consolidation plan. The plan is part of GM's larger restructuring effort to achieve financial viability. The Treasury Department's Task Force is working with GM and its stakeholders to ensure the company becomes more competitive in the long-term. The Task Force was not involved in deciding which dealers would be part of the consolidation plan. The article emphasizes the importance of the President's intervention in saving the GM and Chrysler dealer networks. The Administration is committed to supporting a restructuring that leads to stronger car companies and more stable employment. Efforts will also be made to ensure financing is available to creditworthy dealers and to boost domestic demand for cars.